President Obama called Armenian President Serzh Sargsian and Azerbaijani President Ilham Aliyev ahead of their summit on the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict. He emphasized the need for a peaceful settlement and urged the leaders to finalize and endorse the Basic Principles during their meeting with Russian President Dimitriy Medvedev. Once agreed upon, negotiations can begin based on principles of non-use of force, territorial integrity, and self-determination. President Obama stressed the importance of resolving the conflict for the sake of the people in the region and assured continued support from the United States.